# Josh Sanders: LinkedIn Growth & High-Ticket Education

Josh Sanders (Head of Content for Chris Donnelly) treats LinkedIn as a high-velocity data-engineering lab. This skill focuses on "Format Arbitrage," "Pre-validated Outlier Analysis," and "Depth-First Monetization" to capture attention and convert it into high-ticket ($5k+) educational cohorts.

## Core Methodology

Sanders shifts the focus from vanity metrics to depth metrics (Saves/Reposts) and de-platforming (Newsletter conversion). He views the LinkedIn profile as a high-converting landing page and leverages the "30/30/30/10" commenting system to hijack algorithmic reach before a single post is published. 

His content engine runs on "Pre-Validated Outlier Engineering"—identifying content that has already broken the algorithm for others, and rebuilding it with 10x more depth or in a scroll-stopping format (like the Storytelling Carousel or Cheat Sheet). The free "how-to" builds irrefutable authority, while the "with-you" accountability is monetized in $5k+ cohorts.

